      "*": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p><b><a href=\"/Main_Page\" title=\"Main Page\">Home</a> * <a href=\"/People\" title=\"People\">People</a> * Motohiro Isozaki</b>\n</p>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:252px;\"><a href=\"http://yaneuraou.yaneu.com/2014/12/31/%e4%bb%8a%e5%b9%b4%e4%b8%80%e5%b9%b4%e3%82%92%e6%8c%af%e3%82%8a%e8%bf%94%e3%81%a3%e3%81%a6/\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/images/thumb/9/97/Kasparov201411.jpg/250px-Kasparov201411.jpg\" width=\"250\" height=\"333\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/9/97/Kasparov201411.jpg/375px-Kasparov201411.jpg 1.5x, /images/thumb/9/97/Kasparov201411.jpg/500px-Kasparov201411.jpg 2x\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/File:Kasparov201411.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div><a href=\"/Garry_Kasparov\" title=\"Garry Kasparov\">Garry Kasparov</a> and Motohiro Isozaki <sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup></div></div></div> \n<p><b>Motohiro Isozaki</b>, (やねうらお)<br />\na Japanese <a href=\"/Shogi\" title=\"Shogi\">Shogi</a> programmer from <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Osaka\">Osaka</a>. He is author of <i>Yaneura King</i> <sup id=\"cite_ref-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>, and the <a href=\"/index.php?title=WCSC29&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"WCSC29 (page does not exist)\">29th World Computer Shogi Champion</a> <sup id=\"cite_ref-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup> <a href=\"/YaneuraOu\" title=\"YaneuraOu\">YaneuraOu</a> <sup id=\"cite_ref-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup> <sup id=\"cite_ref-5\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup>. His <i>YaneuraOu Official Website</i> elaborates not only on YaneuraOu, but Shogi engines, and recently, the synergy of the Shogi community with the computer chess and in particular the <a href=\"/Stockfish\" title=\"Stockfish\">Stockfish</a> community, yielding in <a href=\"/NNUE\" title=\"NNUE\">NNUE</a> and <a href=\"/Stockfish_NNUE\" title=\"Stockfish NNUE\">Stockfish NNUE</a> <sup id=\"cite_ref-6\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup>.\n</p>\n<h1><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"External_Links\">External Links</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Motohiro_Isozaki&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: External Links\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h1>\n<ul><li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://yaneuraou.yaneu.com/\">やねうら王 公式サイト | コンピューター将棋 やねうら王 公式サイト YaneuraOu Official Website</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Motohiro Isozaki</a> aka Yaneurao</li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://yaneuraou.yaneu.com/2020/08/21/3-technologies-in-shogi-ai-that-could-be-used-for-chess-ai/\">3 technologies in shogi AI that could be used for chess AI</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Motohiro Isozaki</a>, August 21, 2020&#160;» <a href=\"/Stockfish_NNUE\" title=\"Stockfish NNUE\">Stockfish NNUE</a></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://github.com/yaneurao\">yaneurao (yaneurao) · GitHub</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Motohiro Isozaki</a> aka Yaneurao</li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://github.com/yaneurao/YaneuraOu\">GitHub - yaneurao/YaneuraOu: YaneuraOu is the World's Strongest Shogi engine(AI player), WCSC29 1st winner, educational and USI compliant engine</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Motohiro Isozaki</a> aka Yaneurao</li></ul>\n<h1><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Motohiro_Isozaki&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h1>\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-1\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://yaneuraou.yaneu.com/2014/12/31/%e4%bb%8a%e5%b9%b4%e4%b8%80%e5%b9%b4%e3%82%92%e6%8c%af%e3%82%8a%e8%bf%94%e3%81%a3%e3%81%a6/\">今年一年を振り返って | やねうら王 公式サイト (Looking back this year | Yaneura Oh Official Site)</a>, December 31, 2014</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-2\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a href=\"/Hisayori_Noda\" title=\"Hisayori Noda\">Hisayori Noda</a>, <a href=\"/Jun_Okabe\" title=\"Jun Okabe\">Jun Okabe</a>, <a href=\"/index.php?title=Takahiro_Suzuki&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Takahiro Suzuki (page does not exist)\">Takahiro Suzuki</a>, <a href=\"/Masatoshi_Hidaka\" title=\"Masatoshi Hidaka\">Masatoshi Hidaka</a>, <a href=\"/Yu_Nasu\" title=\"Yu Nasu\">Yu Nasu</a>, <a href=\"/index.php?title=Akio_Kono&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Akio Kono (page does not exist)\">Akio Kono</a> (<b>2017</b>). <i>Shouten Gensou Knights of Tanuki Appeal Document</i>. The Minstrel's Ballad: Tanuki's Reign, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www2.computer-shogi.org/wcsc27/appeal/tanuki-/appeal.pdf\">pdf</a> (Japanese)</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-3\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-3\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www2.computer-shogi.org/wcsc29/\">第29回世界コンピュータ将棋選手権 wcsc29</a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-4\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-4\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://yaneuraou.yaneu.com/\">やねうら王 公式サイト | コンピューター将棋 やねうら王 公式サイト YaneuraOu Official Website</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Motohiro Isozaki</a> aka Yaneurao</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-5\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-5\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://github.com/yaneurao/YaneuraOu\">GitHub - yaneurao/YaneuraOu: YaneuraOu is the World's Strongest Shogi engine(AI player), WCSC29 1st winner, educational and USI compliant engine</a>, hosted by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Motohiro Isozaki</a> aka Yaneurao</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-6\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-6\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://yaneuraou.yaneu.com/2019/06/24/%E5%B0%86%E6%A3%8B%E3%82%BD%E3%83%95%E3%83%88%E9%96%8B%E7%99%BA%E8%80%85%E3%81%8Cstockfish%E3%81%AB%E8%B2%A2%E7%8C%AE%E3%81%99%E3%82%8B%E6%97%A5/\">将棋ソフト開発者がStockfishに貢献する日 The day when shogi software developers contribute to Stockfish</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Motohiro Isozaki</a>, June 2019</span>\n</li>\n</ol></div>\n<p><b><a href=\"/People\" title=\"People\">Up one level</a></b>\n</p>\n<!-- \nNewPP limit report\nCached time: 20260228174746\nCache expiry: 86400\nDynamic content: false\nCPU time usage: 0.016 seconds\nReal time usage: 0.017 seconds\nPreprocessor visited node count: 95/1000000\nPreprocessor generated node count: 222/1000000\nPost‐expand include size: 0/2097152 bytes\nTemplate argument size: 0/2097152 bytes\nHighest expansion depth: 2/40\nExpensive parser function count: 0/100\n-->\n<!--\nTransclusion expansion time report (%,ms,calls,template)\n100.00%    0.000      1 -total\n-->\n</div>\n<!-- Saved in parser cache with key oscar70_mw1-mw_:pcache:idhash:7403-0!canonical and timestamp 20260228174746 and revision id 24645\n -->\n"
